Program: Outlook
Title: 26/09/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00k7yzy
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 27 Sep 2011
Lily Ramirez is married to the oldest of the trapped Chilean miners, Mario Gomez. After the rescue, they were led to expect book deals and Hollywood movies but the reality has been quite different. Mario hasn't gone back to work because of his health, and the couple have been surviving on a state pension. Also, we hear about life at the world's largest refugee camp - Dadaab in Northern Kenya. And, why lottery winner Charmaine Watson decided to spend part of her winning on fighting bullying by investing in a musical that tackles the issue. Show less